&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; He sets his friend down gently onto a platform and then collapses himself.
&gt; His breath is labored yet he is still able to keep himself online.  And even
&gt; in his compromised state, he still carries an air of his famous temperament,
&gt; as he narrows his eyes with a low growl in his voice.

&lt;NEW&gt;

As TUSCON got on board the ship BUMP and SANTON were there to greet
him as he landed. They carefully took SILVERBOLT from him and laid him
on a suspensor bed and moved him to the side.

BUMP hooked a energon feed tube to TUSCON so that he could regain his
energon as quickly as possible while SANTON began to look over
SILVERBOLT. He shook his head. &quot;He is still alive, but we but we need
to get him back to the ark.&quot;

&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &quot; About Rodimus...  If he chose to turn on our faction, then so be it.
&gt; Instead of taking the initiative to fend off the temptation, he has opted
&gt; for an easy way out instead.  I did what I could to save him!  I can not do
&gt; any more than that! &quot;
&gt;
&gt; He snaps his tail in annoyance.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; He has no sense of responsibility, self confidence, or the ineptitude to
&gt; overcome a major adversity!  Of course he is vulnerable to possession!  HE
&gt; WANTS IT THAT WAY, IT&#39;S THE EASIEST WAY AROUND A DIFFICULT SITUATION!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He slaps a heavy front paw down on the shuttle floor.  Now exhausted, he
&gt; tries to catch his breath. Yet he looks to Leo Prime as he fights to keep
&gt; his head and long neck up off the shuttle floor.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Leo Prime, the best thing to do is to relinquish his Prime status and
&gt; revert him back to Hot Rod, where he can do no harm.  From now on, until I
&gt; am restored, I ask that you assume all leadership duties while I recover.
&gt; Promise me you will - do as I request?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He can no longer hold up his head and lays it back on the floor.  Yet he
&gt; looks to Stanton while conversing with Leo Prime.  It was clear to him that
&gt; Rodimus was quite comfortable where he was and that now it was time to do
&gt; something about him.  The silver dragon hardens to the idea of having to
&gt; fight against a friend who now proves to be his greatest foe.  A look of
&gt; sheer determination covers his face as he remains grounded for the time
&gt; being.

&lt;NEW&gt;

&quot;Of course.&quot; LEO PRIME said calmly over the comlink. Almost as if LEO
PRIME could hear his thoughts he said, &quot;We all have weaknesses and
foilbles and things that cause us to do things that we would not
ordinarilly want or desire to do.&quot; There was a thoughtful pause from
LEO PRIME, &quot;But sometimes our greatest foe is not the enemy without,
but we ourselves.&quot;

LEO paused again and then said, &quot;Rest. I think we all need to discuss
this with calmer heads. I will see you when you get back to the Ark.&quot;

Even as TUSCON was getting that rest the shuttle was turned back to
the Ark, SILVERBOLT was a priority. The other FUZORS and TALON would
have to make it for a little while longer.

